Tammy Petersen, News24Barry Leonard (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Hermanus - A search for a 20-year-old man last seen near the old harbour in Hermanus on Saturday resumed on Sunday, the NSRI said.National Sea Rescue Institute spokesperson Craig Lambinon said police were helping them in their search for Barry Leonard."The family had launched a search when Barry failed to return home on the early hours of Saturday morning. He was last seen walking down to the old Hermanus harbour at around 02:00."The NSRI was searching the sea and shoreline near the old harbour.Anyone with information on the man's whereabouts has been asked to phone Hermanus police on 028 313 5300.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.